gobblin.writer.partitioner

Class TimeBasedAvroWriterPartitioner

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.writer.partitioner.TimeBasedWriterPartitioner<GenericRecord>
      • gobblin.writer.partitioner.TimeBasedAvroWriterPartitioner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WriterPartitioner<GenericRecord>

    public class TimeBasedAvroWriterPartitioner
extends TimeBasedWriterPartitioner<GenericRecord>
    A TimeBasedWriterPartitioner for GenericRecords. The Schema.Field that contains the timestamp can be specified using WRITER_PARTITION_COLUMNS, and multiple values can be specified, e.g., "header.timestamp,device.timestamp". If multiple values are specified, they will be tried in order. In the above example, if a record contains a valid "header.timestamp" field, its value will be used, otherwise "device.timestamp" will be used. If a record contains none of the specified fields, or if no field is specified, the current timestamp will be used.
